15/04/2004
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- The UN tribunal announced on Wednesday (14 April) that Slobodan Milosevic has submitted a list of 1,631 witnesses he intends to call when his trial resumes in June. A spokesman said the judges would have the final say on the actual number of people who would testify. The content of the list was not made public.
In other news, Scottish judge Lord Bonomy has been formally appointed a member of the panel hearing Milosevic's case. He will replace Richard May, who resigned for health reasons. (AP, AFP - 14/04/04)
